JOS – Executive Director of League for Human Rights, Dr. Nankin Bagudu has called on APC Delegates to cast their votes for Dr. Fayemi Kayode at the forthcoming Presidential primary election of All Progressives’ Congress billed for Eagle Square in Abuja. Dr Bagudu in an interview with newsmen in Jos said Dr Kayode has laid out plans for Nigeria electorates and delegates of his party. According to him, Nigeria challenges are enormous and the stakes are high. -Advertisement- He said Dr. Kayode has outlined what he intends to do for the people of Nigeria in terms of Security, mineral development, Tourism, Equity and Justice including fairness and Inclusiveness. Bagudu added that given the opportunity, Dr Kayode who is the chairman of Nigeria Governors Forum has the capacity to deliver dividends of democracy to the people of Nigeria. “Kayode has proven that from his experience as Ex Governor and Minister, he is the best material that can salvage this country from the challenges we are facing in this country.” On which of the geo political zone of the country should produce the next Nigeria President come 2023, Dr Bagudu said since this country has been built on the foundation moving power from the the North to the South, in 2015, the Southerners agreed that the political power should move from the South and that after 8 years, power should move back the South, wondering Why political actors are now singing a new song that Power should be thrown open to all to contest. Bagudu added that Southerners should not be made to look like fools. POLL He stressed that it may be difficult for Northern Presidential candidate of any political party may find it difficult to go to the South to campaign and be accepted. He urged Northern political elite to be fair to the people of Southern Nigeria to produce the next President because nobody is first and second class citizen of this country.